cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper proposes a new type theory which extends HoTT, a foundational theory for computer science and mathematics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a new type theory which can be used to define and reason about programming languages. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper deals with the construction of "infinite structures" which can be considered as information-theoretic objects. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper deals with the construction of semi-simplicial types and formalising constructions of Reedy fibrant diagrams, which are objects of study in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper deals with decidability of type checking, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory.
